<subSubSection id="4FB80691E82D45775EFF7CF606664A8B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="38F7DEA2E395D6483AD7E5F8D6761EB6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B66B506E0A5092461DC10089FD8C3DD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
2.9 mm long (mean = 2.9 mm; n = 3); 2.23
<normalizedToken id="E5F35C75443902CB42A6A9C3910DA1C4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the mesonotal mycangial tuft the length of the scutellum; elytral disc flat; declivital interstriae punctate; declivital posterolateral margin carinate to interstriae 5; declivity moderately bisulcate; declivital margins ornamented by only two small sharp incurved spines at the base of interstriae 2 and 3; and declivital interstriae bearing fine erect hair-like setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
